# Rust build artifacts
target/

# Workspace-root /Cargo.lock IS tracked for reproducibility (required by
# PHASE3_SLICE3_REPRO_PLAN.md sub-tasks 2 + 4). Stray sub-crate lockfiles
# (workspace members + excluded sub-projects like
# electrum_plugin/harmonypir-python) shouldn't be tracked — Cargo writes
# a single root lockfile for the workspace, and excluded sub-projects
# have their own reproducibility story.
#
# vendor/**/Cargo.lock IS tracked: cargo vendor emits a per-crate
# Cargo.lock and each vendored crate's .cargo-checksum.json references
# its hash. Dropping these breaks fresh-clone offline builds with
# "failed to calculate checksum of: vendor/<crate>/Cargo.lock".
Cargo.lock
!/Cargo.lock
!vendor/**/Cargo.lock

